feat: enhance stories & news, gallery layout, settings media upload, and volunteer linkedin integration

Frontend:
- Blog & News Page:
  - Created a responsive 'ArticleModal' component to view complete articles/stories in a blurred backdrop overlay.
  - Implemented keyboard listeners (Escape key) and body scroll locking when the modal is active.
  - Standardized all cards in the grid to maintain uniform equal height and width constraints.
  - Added line-clamping on card titles (max 2 lines) and excerpts (max 2 lines with ellipsis '...') to prevent text shifts.
  - Placed 'Read Article' and 'Read Story' buttons pinned to the card footers.
  - Restructured layout using alternating section tones (tone="base" and tone="alt") for clean visual boundaries.
- Founder Message & Site Settings:
  - Added form-data upload support for 'founderImage' inside Admin settings dashboard.
  - Rendered the founder's profile picture inside the home page green circle and the about page portrait frame.
  - Added robust flatMap parser on both pages to split text paragraphs safely on newlines.
- Gallery Page:
  - Enabled dynamic aspect-ratio support on card items (1:1, 4:3, 3:4) using saved ratio metadata.
  - Encased cards in a framed white border, with tight padding (6px on desktop, 5px on mobile) and custom shadows.
  - Created a fully interactive full-screen Lightbox slider with navigation arrows and keyboard controls (Left/Right/Esc).
  - Improved responsiveness: configured grid to stack cards to a single column under 480px width.
- Volunteer Team Page:
  - Rendered a branded LinkedIn social icon button on volunteer cards linking to their profile.
  - Styled hover states with blue fill backgrounds, translation shifts, and shadow lifts.
  - Included a LinkedIn profile URL field in the Admin team form.

Backend:
- Settings:
  - Added 'founderImage' and 'imagePublicId' properties to Settings Schema.
  - Integrated multer and Cloudinary upload support inside PUT /settings route.
  - Added a regular expression split parser (/\r?\n\r?\n/) to support CRLF and LF newlines during settings save.
- Volunteer Member:
  - Added 'linkedin' URL string property to VolunteerMember Schema.
